abstract: Court filings reveal that total of 113 Florida State University students reported being sexually assaulted in 2014 to school's Victim Advocate Office; college informed federal authorities of only 14 such incidents.
lead_paragraph: The university reported only 14 of 113 cases of student-reported rape to the federal government because many of the reported assaults occurred off-campus.

headline.main: F.S.U. Reported Few Rape Cases to the U.S.
headline.print_headline: Ex-Official Says F.S.U. Reported Few Rapes
